I prefer systems that work right off the bat, the box works, something
talks, and how do I make it better. Just in that attempt there&#39;s lots of
tail chasing, I don&#39;t like to get sidetracked on other systems--unless
there&#39;s already something to suggest it works better. It&#39;s been my
expereince that all that is needed is something that has human speech
frequencies which can be rearranged in to &quot;thier&quot; voices. Various methods of
providing the raw audio has been proven to work, that&#39;s why I focus on that
appraoch.  White noise, radio between stations, running water, foreign
language, EVPmaker, and the box, all the same concept.

 Yeah, the thing about all the fake mediums is right, and there&#39;s no
shortage of people that throw money desperately seeking that shread of proof
that they personally go on. I think that is the bottom line, people are so
absolutely scared of death thay want *any* reassurance. Money is no object.

 Frank-S

